<title>USA: U.S. mortgage application volume fell in latest wk.</title>
<headline>U.S. mortgage application volume fell in latest wk.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The volume of total U.S. mortgage applications fell 1.3 percent in the week ending August 16, according to a Mortgage Bankers Association of America weekly survey.</p>
<p>Specifically, the volume of applications to refinance mortgages fell 2.7 percent in the latest survey week, while applications to purchase mortgages fell 0.9 percent.</p>
<p>The seasonally adjusted refinancing index fell 2.7 percent to 279.9 from 287.8 the previous week, it said.</p>
<p>The purchase index rose 0.7 percent to 177.6 in the latest survey from 176.3 in the previous week, it said.  </p>
